President Obama has announced the recipients of the National Medal of Science and the National Medal of Technology and Innovation. The National Medal of Science recognizes individuals who have made outstanding contributions to science and engineering, while the National Medal of Technology and Innovation honors those who have made lasting contributions to America's competitiveness and quality of life. The recipients will receive their awards at a White House ceremony later this year. Additionally, the White House will host the 2010 White House Science Fair to celebrate winners of various science, technology, engineering, and math competitions.